FBIS3-9081 "dreeu054_i_94008" FBIS-EEU-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Mar 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA TANJUG on UN Response LD1903214494 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2132 GMT 19 Mar 94 LD1903214494 Belgrade TANJUG Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Belgrade, March 19 (TANJUG) -- A U.N. officer has resolutely denied allegations by Moslem authorities in Sarajevo that the explosion that left three persons wounded in the Alipasino Polje suburb on Saturday was caused by a Serb mortar shell. Lieutenant-Colonel [name indistinct] Pernod of the French battalion within the U.N. Protection Force in war-torn Bosnia-Herzegovina said that the explosion was the result of a rifle-launched grenade, the AFP reports. The maximum range of such a grenade is 600 metres and the nearest Serb positions are 1,500 metres away from the place where the explosion occurred, Pernod specified.
